I had a dream about you last night in which I saw you as I remembered you
over the years, from a little kid when we went to camp through to your last
visit in NYC. Through it all, in every instance, I was awestruck by your
kindness, your warmth, your generosity and lack of judgement. I woke up
realizing I'd never told you what your friendship meant to me and how much
it informed who I try to be now, every day.

So I figured I'd write and tell you. We don't talk much these days; we live
on opposite sides of the country and have totally different lives, but I
wanted you to know that you changed someone's life for the better just by
being you.

Thanks!
Josh

